GRADLE: Built automation system thatuses a groovy-based DLS.
MAVEN: Software project management system that is primarily used for Jave.

GRADLE: Doesn't use an XML file for declaring the project configuration.
MAVEN: Uses XML file for declaring the project, its dependencies, the build order, and it required plugin.

GRADLE: Based on a graph of task dependencies that do the work.
MAVEN: Based on a phases of the fixed and linear model.
